            "type": "text",
            "text": "Understanding Nanonets OCR S Architecture"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Nanonets OCR S (Nanonets_Ocr_S_F16) is designed for efficient OCR tasks with F16 precision, balancing accuracy and speed. It supports multiple languages and document types, making it suitable for diverse API applications. Key features include low-latency inference and compatibility with standard ML frameworks."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "API Integration with nanonets/nanonets-ocr-a hugging face"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Integrating nanonets/nanonets-ocr-a hugging face involves setting up RESTful endpoints or SDKs. Start by loading the model via Hugging Face's transformers library, then wrap it in an API service using frameworks like FastAPI or Flask. Ensure proper error handling and authentication for secure access. Example code snippet:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code_block",
        "lang": "python",
        "value": "from transformers import AutoModelForTokenClassification\nmodel = AutoModelForTokenClassification.from_pretrained(\"nanonets/nanonets-ocr-a\")",
        "children": [
          {
